1
00:00:20,700 --> 00:00:33,780
BARRACUDA, BLUE MARLIN and red snapper were for sale before Christmas at Millie Ifill fish market, but only to those who observed pandemic protocol:“No Mask No Service”, said a large sign.

2
00:00:34,440 --> 00:00:41,070
Local discipline and tests on travellers kept covid-19 cases in Barbados to a trickle.

3
00:00:41,620 --> 00:00:45,440
After a lockdown, bars and boutiques were doing brisk business.

4
00:00:45,770 --> 00:00:51,459
Reservations at restaurants such as the Fish Pot at Little Good Harbour were becoming hard to get.

5
00:00:51,870 --> 00:00:55,210
Locals said the island was in its own little bubble.

6
00:00:55,810 --> 00:00:57,530
The bubble has burst.

7
00:00:58,080 --> 00:01:03,610
On December 31st the government scuppered“Old Year’s Night”fireworks parties.

8
00:01:04,070 --> 00:01:10,479
A curfew extends from 9pm to 5am, to contain a surge in infections.

9
00:01:10,969 --> 00:01:15,710
Nearby St Vincent has declared Barbados a“high-risk country”.

10
00:01:16,560 --> 00:01:17,920
Two things went wrong.

11
00:01:18,250 --> 00:01:21,899
First, cracks appeared in the controls on travellers.

12
00:01:22,420 --> 00:01:32,590
Passengers to Barbados must test negative for covid-19 before flying andremain in quarantine until their second negative test.

13
00:01:33,120 --> 00:01:38,600
As holiday traffic picked up, so did the numbers testing positive after arrival.

14
00:01:39,309 --> 00:01:41,090
A few have broken the rules.

15
00:01:41,389 --> 00:01:59,520
On December 29th Zara Holland, a former Miss Great Britain who was also a contestant on“Love Island”, a reality-TV dating show, and her partner, Elliot Love, allegedly removed the red warning bracelets put on them after Mr Love tested positive.

16
00:02:00,139 --> 00:02:03,630
They were apprehended trying to board a flight to London.

17
00:02:04,299 --> 00:02:08,120
Ms Holland has apologised“to the entire country of Barbados”.

18
00:02:08,540 --> 00:02:16,050
She has been sentenced to pay a fine of B$12,000 ($6,000).

19
00:02:16,900 --> 00:02:19,860
Second, the virus has spread locally.

20
00:02:20,230 --> 00:02:25,629
On December 26th several prison guards took part in a“bus crawl”.

21
00:02:26,290 --> 00:02:36,430
These are advertised with raunchy names such as“brandy & punanny”(pussy), and involve open-sided buses and stops at bars and rum shops.

22
00:02:36,929 --> 00:02:40,600
The Boxing Day jolly seems to have been a super-spreader.

23
00:02:48,520 --> 00:02:54,940
The opposition blames the government for failing to close the border to people from high-risk countries.

24
00:02:55,309 --> 00:03:01,420
Grenada and Jamaica stopped flights from Britain, because of its rampant new strain of the virus.

25
00:03:02,390 --> 00:03:07,090
Barbados depends more on visitors from Britain than do most other islands.

26
00:03:07,480 --> 00:03:12,710
Its prime minister, Mia Mottley, has urged Barbadians to get“more serious”.

27
00:03:13,219 --> 00:03:15,000
Bus crawls are now banned.

28
00:03:15,410 --> 00:03:18,839
Tamper-proof bracelets are replacing cloth ones.

29
00:03:19,310 --> 00:03:21,140
Quarantine rules are tighter.

30
00:03:21,870 --> 00:03:27,080
Barbados has learned that bubbles and bus crawls don’t mix.

